    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix heap buffer overflow in nr_fapi_p7_utils dump_harq_0_1 function\n\n### Summary\nThe `dump_harq_0_1` function in `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c` was accessing `harq_list` array elements without proper bounds checking or NULL pointer validation. This caused heap buffer overflows when `num_harq` contained invalid values or when `harq_list` was NULL, leading to segmentation faults during UCI indication processing.\n\nThe issue occurred because the function directly accessed `harq_list[i]` without validating that:\n1. `harq_list` pointer is not NULL\n2. `num_harq` doesn't exceed the allocated size of the array\n3. `i` stays within valid bounds\n\nSimilar issues were found in the `eq_uci_indication_harq_pdu_0_1` and `copy_uci_indication_harq_pdu_0_1` functions that process the same structure.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: \n  - Added validation in `dump_harq_0_1` to check `harq->num_harq > 8` and `harq->harq_list == NULL` before accessing array elements\n  - Added validation in `eq_uci_indication_harq_pdu_0_1` to check both `a->num_harq > 8` and `b->num_harq > 8` and NULL pointer checks for both `harq_list` pointers\n  - Added validation in `copy_uci_indication_harq_pdu_0_1` to check `src->num_harq > 8` and NULL pointer checks for both `src->harq_list` and `dst->harq_list`\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/inc/nr_fapi_p7_utils.h`: Created header file with function declarations\n\n"
}